    "The linear approach of CAV allows the model to determine that 'Stripe' is an important concept for identifying 'Zebra,' but what if we have other classes with 'Stripes,' such as 'Tiger, Lion'?",
    "CAR, try to generalise CAV to nonlinear decisions rather than linear ones and provide an accurate explanation.",
    "CoherencyIndicates that samples from one class of concepts must be similar while being dissimilar to samples from another class of concepts.",
    "For example, in terms of bird species identification data [102], there is a concept of 'wing' that contains various samples of wings that differ from the concept of 'leg'.",
    "Clustering methods such as K-Means [145], U-K-Means [193],Contrastive Clustering [194], and DeepClustering [195] can achieve coherency."
